OL,5,F"Because we all have a disability here
OL,6,Fwe understand each other. We all have
OL,7,Feach other's backs and it's not just a
OL,8,Fjob to me anymore."
OL,10,F#1.7m was invested into Ballycopeland
OL,11,FWindmill and cafe in 2022.
OL,13,FMost of that funding was from the
OL,14,FDepartment for Communities. Ulster
OL,15,FSupported Employment Limited, or USEL,
OL,16,Fmanages the site and employees.
OL,18,FThe local community association has
OL,19,Fwritten to Communities Minister Gordon
OL,20,FLyons calling for support to keep the
OL,21,Fcafe open.
